  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WHO Strategic Advisory Group of Experts activities and use of SAGE data</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The World Health Organization is contracting with HelpAge to support the WHO SAGE team in the dissemination and use of its results to inform policy. This includes liaison with country and WHO SAGE teams, and with stakeholders in countries, to facilitate study implementation, data dissemination and shaping results into policy relevant materials. This may also include presentation of results at national and international meetings, active embedding of results through linkages with policy makers, and publication of  papers and policy briefs.   This work will include:   1. undertaking literature reviews related to health and ageing in the respective countries;   2. conducting literature reviews on health and ageing with an emphaisis on health systems responses to ageing, universal health coverage and integrated people centred care;   3. pursuing cross-study data harmonization between SAGE and other available studies in each country and planned longitudinal studies on ageing especially in LMICs;   4. working with WHO SAGE to extend scope for presenting results at conferences/meetings in national, regional and international settings;   5. providing regular updates and progress reports to WHO SAGE team and assisting with compiling information for donor reporting; and,   6. assisting with writing of reports and manuscripts for publication.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To assist with Wave 2 report preparations, policy briefs and manuscripts for publication using SAGE W2 data in collaboration with the WHO SAGE team and country study teams</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To collate available data sets for harmonization</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To facilitate and undertake data analyses</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To support literature review outputs/summaries</narrative>
  </description>
